      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and we do sacrifice unto him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] so R.V. text. R.V. margin. ‘Another reading is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "yet we do no sacrifice since &c",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".’ The Hebrew words for “unto him” and “not” though written with a different second letter are pronounced in the same way, ‘lô’. The context as a rule makes it easy to distinguish the meaning. But there are some ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
