        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " instances, in which the Hebrew Bibles preserve the tradition of confusion between the two words. It is even possible that the word ‘lô’ (‘unto him’) may have sometimes been written with the same second letter as the negative (e.g. ",
        "children": []
