      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "external",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " evidence is in favour of the pronoun ‘unto him’, being supported by the K’ri, by the LXX. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αὐτῷ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), the Vulgate (‘nos immolabimus victimas’ without a negative), the Syriac, Versions and by the parallel text in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Es 5:69",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (‘and do sacrifice unto him’).",
